<item>
            <title>[LU-12228] lfs find negative options</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12228</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;while checking for lfs find parameters of a PFL file, if at least 1 component matches then the file matches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;however negation of it is !(at least 1 component matches) = no one component matches, &lt;br/&gt;
i.e. not &quot;at least one component does not match&#8221; - what is checked now in some cases now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. having stripe size 1M, 2M for 2 components and searching:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; lfs find ! -S 2M /mnt/lustre&lt;br/&gt;
this file should not be found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;presumably all the fp_exclude_* options are involved which are passed to find_value_cmp.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
